Preheat the #oven{} to 180°C. Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125}. Trim the root from the @Baby Gem Lettuce{2} and separate the leaves. Halve the @Lemon{½}.

Peel the @Garlic Clove{1} and pop into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Scrunch to enclose it. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Pop aside once cooked and allow to cool.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} over medium high heat. Once hot, add the @British Chicken Thighs{3}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes} each side. Once browned, pop onto a low sided #baking tray{} and roast until cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Remove the roasted garlic from the foil and mash with a #fork{} until smooth. In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Mayonnaise{2}, @Dijon Mustard{½}(see ingredients for amount), the roasted garlic and three quarters of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40}. Squeeze in the lemon juice and mix in the @olive oil for the Dressing{2} and @Water{30}. Mix until well combined. Season to taste with salt and pepper and keep to one side.

Do any washing up that needs doing whilst you have time. Transfer the lettuce leaves to a large #bowl{} and add the tomatoes along with half of the dressing. Mix well to coat.

Once the chicken is cooked, leave to rest for a few minutes before thinly slicing. Divide the lettuce and tomatoes between your plates then top with the sliced chicken. Sprinkle on the @Croutons{1}, remaining cheese and drizzle over the remaining dressing. Enjoy!